 officers  branding  stores  credit and store cards  gallery  arms  see also  references  further reading  external links historyedit david jones and coy store corner of george street and barrack lane circa  david jones a welsh merchant met a hobart businessman charles appleton in london appleton had established a store in sydney in  and jones subsequently established a partnership with appleton moved to australia in  and the sydney store became known as appleton  jones when the partnership was dissolved in  jones moved his business to premises on the corner of george street and barrack lane jones survived the depression of the s and by  had retired from active management of the business a few years later when the firm failed he returned to manage its affairs and in a few years had fully discharged all obligations to his creditors by  the george street store had been rebuilt and a mail order facility introduced a factory was opened in marlborough street sydney to reduce reliance on imported goods on the death of the founder his son edward lloyd jones – led the company at eighteen years of age edward lloyd jones jnr – journeyed to england and entered the london office of david jones on his return to australia he gained pastoral and cattle experience in the burnett district of queensland he reentered the family business upon the death of his father in the train disaster at redfern in  david jones was then a private company but in  it became a public company edward lloyd jones jnr became chairman of directors and held that position until he resigned in  the elizabeth street store was opened in  under the guidance of chairman charles lloyd jones a further store was opened in market street sydney in  there was a small branch located in the australia hotel on martin place in  a state banquet was held for visiting queen elizabeth ii in the restaurant of the elizabeth street store s  sedit david jones flagship building on the corner of elizabeth street  market street sydney regional nsw  interstate entryedit within new south wales david jones established its first store in newcastle by acquiring scotts on hunter street in  closed  and  in wollongong the retailer walter lance  co in  david jones acquired and then converted the big w department stores at kotara fair and the two storey big w at warrawong in  the warrawong store closed in february  there was a store in wagga wagga due to the purchase of david copland  co in  closed  david jones expanded into victoria in  by acquiring the three stores of buckley  nunn located in bourke street northland and chadstone closed the latter in  in  david jones purchased the former gj coles store and building at  bourke street melbourne converting it into a david jones store david jones also owned the former georges store in collins street melbourne between  and  in south australia there were the acquisitions of charles birks  co adelaide in  and john martins adelaide in  in western australia acquired bon marche perth in  closed  foy  gibson in  closed  and aherns perth in  in queensland david jones purchased finney isles brisbane in  mckimmons townsville in  relocated from flinders street and then closed in  tc beirne brisbane in  marsh  webster mackay in  closed  bolands cairns also in  relocated to earlsville in  since closed wyper bros bundaberg in  closed  and stuparts maryborough in  closed  united statesedit in  david jones acquired a group of  stores in the united states called buffums these were ultimately rolled into adelaide steamship company and closed by that company in may  david jones art galleryedit a significant feature of the elizabeth street shop contributing greatly to its aura of quality and exclusivity was the david jones art gallery founded in  directors included will ashton – marion hall best – john amory – m p ferrandiere – george duncan – robert haines – brian moore – and peta phillips  among the many drawcards was the dobell exhibition of  the duke of bedfords collection in  and the mendel collection of modern painting also in  many of the prominent arts societies which held annual exhibitions there included the australian art society the society of artists australian watercolour institute contemporary art society and society of sculptors and associates prize exhibitions held in the gallery included those sponsored by w d  h o wills and transfield dajonians repertory societyedit throughout the s and s the sydney store supported the dajonians repertory society a staff club amateur theatre group their plays were variously performed in the david jones theatrette and such theatres as st james hall and independent theatre they engaged the services of a permanent producer carl francis throughout the s and frederick hughes from  and produced six plays a year mostly light comedies by recognised playwrights such as j b priestley through this time the company was led by sir charles lloyd jones until his death in  by  the store network had expanded to eight stores with expansion focused upon the burgeoning new suburbs of sydney s  sedit in  the adelaide steamship company headed by john spalvins acquired a substantial interest in david jones culminating in a complete takeover that took the company out of the jones family hands for the first time in its history through the s and into the s the two companies involved themselves in a complex company structure whereby they each owned about half of each other and financed by huge borrowings acquired a portfolio of other companies other acquisitions made by adelaide steamship included petersville sleigh tooth  co penfolds and numerous others the recession of the early s caused the nervous lenders over  banks to demand the return of their assets this forced the liquidation of the portfolio at firesale prices and led the two companies into bankruptcy the worthless adelaide steamship company was renamed residual assco ltd and was delisted the worthless david jones limited was renamed djl a number of the assets with value were very successfully sold off via public floats in particular national foods woolworths and the department store assets of djl were floated as david jones limited in  david jones announced an  million public float of the david jones and john martin retail operations the new david jones limited was subsequently listed on the australian stock exchange with a new asx code of djs the separation and public float of the department store assets in  resulted in structural and cultural changes which saw periods of stagnancy and high staff turnover changes in management saw djs falter in the late s shares initially offered at a fell as low as a s  presentedit a major strategic review in  saw the closing of two unprofitable stores the lossmaking david jones online webbased business and its gourmet food retail stores foodchain it revitalised many of its stores including its flagship elizabeth street and market street stores in sydney two individual buildings linked both underground and via air bridge through westfield sydney during this period sales growth and profit growth were not continually increasing despite a consumer spending boom and the securing of exclusive deals with australian and international brands in this period the share price was volatile it reached a high of over  the global downturn in  affected david jones reporting a sales decline of  to m in the first half of  in june  ceo mark mcinnes resigned after allegations that he had sexually harassed a female employee mcinnes successor paul zahra led the company through significant restructuring including the expansion of the online retail presence until october  when he announced that his intention to resign zahra retained his position however on account of strong shareholder support against board chairman peter mason who eventually resigned along with two other directors who had been accused of insider trading proposed myer mergeredit in october  myer approached david jones with a conditional nonbinding indicative proposal for a potential merger of the two companies myer believed the combined group would have generated pro forma sales and earnings before interest and tax in  of approximately  billion and  million respectively in addition myer expected that a merger could have achieved more than  million of ongoing annual cost synergies within three years primarily driven by structural efficiencies the board of david jones rejected the offer in november  in february  myer again approached david jones offering to buy the company at market value with david jones having a market capitalisation of  billion myer also indicated that its reappointed chief executive bernie brookes would be capable of managing the combined entity should the merger occur david jones acknowledged the letter stating it would consider any proposal that is in the best interest of its shareholders but made no further comment takeover by woolworths south africaedit in april  myer withdrew its proposed merger of equals following on from david jones announcement that it had recommended a  cash per share proposal and entered into a scheme implementation deed with south africanbased retail group woolworths implying a market capitalisation of  billion the takeover bid was approved in july  by the federal court of australia in midaugust  despite the previously stated intention by woolworths to retain ceo paul zahra zahra announced his resignation once more amid indications of significant differences between strategy and the future of the company giving three months notice to ensure a smooth handover woolworths then announced that country road ceo iain nairn would succeed zahra as chief executive following the takeover to fund in part the purchase woolworths south africa has offered for sale the iconic  market street store this will result in the closure of the store the eight floors of homewares furniture electricals and menswear will be merged into the existing nine floors elizabeth street store it is not clear if the food hall will be retained as part of the merger into the elizabeth street store entry into new zealandedit in july  the wellington new zealand department store kirkcaldie  stains agreed to be purchased by woolworths south africa the existing wellington store closed in  it reopened on  july  as the first david jones store in new zealand the store fit out has cost ca aumn more than originally budgeted the david jones website does not provide delivery to new zealand remaining a solely australian trading website managementedit sir charles lloyd jones scion of the jones family and chairman of david jones ltd from  until his death in  executive chairmenedit david jones – edward lloyd jones – edward lloyd jones jnr – sir charles lloyd jones – david lloyd jones – charles lloyd jones jnr – nonexecutive chairmenedit dick warburton – bob savage – peter mason – gordon cairns –date chief executive officersedit john spalvins – rod mewing – chris tideman – peter wilkinson – mark mcinnes – paul zahra – iain nairn – john dixon –date brandingedit model miranda kerr seated at a david jones book signing in sydney kerr was the spokesperson of the company from  until  david jones branding—a blackonwhite houndstooth pattern—is one of the most recognised corporate identities in australia a government sponsored panel judged it in  as one of australias top ten favourite trade marks the iconic design was the result of a  rebranding exercise by charles lloyd jones jnr who desired that the store would be so well known by the design as to not require the use of the name on the packing it was inspired allegedly from the houndstooth design on a miss dior perfume bottle of his mothers hannah jones on  july  david jones introduced a new logo with a revised font style and removed references to the houndstooth online slogans have been used for sometime at david jones often the slogans have been used for multiple decades and have become the definition of the david jones offer for a generation past slogans include for service s theres no other store like david jones s and s the most beautiful store in the world s was is always s live an extraordinary life  david jones has for some decades used models and personalities as a way of creating cut through in advertising in the late th century it was maureen duval who also hosted good morning sydney part sponsored by david jones on ten sydney in the current century there have been new models used including megan gale miranda kerr and jessica gomes kerr worked for the retailer from  until  on march   model jessica gomes was announced as kerrs replacement celebrities used by david jones in recent times include liz hurley and kim cattrall five stores have food halls which are viewed as a key part of the david jones brand emphasising quality and style yet have come under recent criticism the failed foodchain experiment—effectively a smaller chain of standalone food halls—was sold to the parent company of freedom furniture in  after it proved unprofitable it was announced in july  neil perry a food service and restaurant operator will consult to david jones on the new food halls including assortment presentation and service storesedit elizabeth street entrance in sydney david jones has department stores in all australian capital cities except hobart and darwin and also has stores in kotara newcastle tuggerah wollongong and robina and broadbeach waters gold coast stores are located in city centre retail areas and enclosed shopping centres in  david jones recast its criteria for store locations reflecting ceo mark mcinnes intention to concentrate on low risk high value locations stores in sydney at centro bankstown closed july  and westfield eastgardens october  were replaced by myer however david jones replaced the myer store in westfield burwood in may  and opened a new store at westfield chermside in august  and a new store at queensplaza brisbane in february  the melbourne bourke street stores were completely renovated in mid at a cost of  million in january  david jones announced that the claremont store would be closed in  to allow for a complete rebuilding to reopen in  the new store increased floor space by  david jones opened a new format fashion focused format in malvern victoria on  september  on the st of may  david jones opened in indooroopilly queensland in october  david jones opened in macquarie centre at the same time a number of foreign retailers opened in the centre including hm zara and uniqlo in march  the new owners of david jones woolworths south africa announced they will sell off and close the nine floor market street sydney store housing the home food and menswear departments the market street store was opened in  as part of this transition in  the christmas shop was moved from th floor market street to the lower ground of elizabeth street david jones currently has  stores in australia credit and store cardsedit david jones derives about  per cent of its annual earnings from its store cards in february  it announced it would be launching a david jones american express card before christmas  and would transfer its  million store card receivables representing  cardholders to american express it is also considering additional financial services such as insurance and home loans under its brand financial services is a highly profitable division for david jones and in fy contributed earnings of  million the introduction of the david jones american express platinum card as well as an alliance with the qantas frequent flyer programme in  has contributed to the growth of this division however in march  the company had announced that the david jonesamerican express alliance converts to a share of actual profits in fy and subsequently the company saw its share of ebit generated by this business at broadly half of the contribution generated in  galleryedit david jones previous logo featuring the theres no other store like slogan david jones at woden town centre in canberra david jones  second floor at queensplaza in brisbane queen street mall end david jones  second floor at queensplaza in brisbane adelaide street end the former david jones melbourne redeveloped in  the foodhall at david jones market street david jones florist at david jones elizabeth street armsedit arms of david jones limited notes the arms of david jones limited adopted in  consist of crest on a wreath or and gules a dragons head erased sable between two fleursdelys or escutcheon checky alternate or and checky argent and sable two flaunches azure on each a fleursdelys or supporters on the dexter side a dragon gules winged argent and on the sinister side a kangaroo proper motto sedula cura attentive care symbolism in the shield the subdivisions represent the departments of a department store the checky portions represent accounting the flaunches are drawn from the jones family arms see alsoedit bolands centre referencesedit  a b sales report preliminary group results announcement pdf retrieved  august    whl  integrated report pdf retrieved  october    a b c story of david jones david jones archived from the original on  april  retrieved  may    company history answerscom retrieved on  july   catherine harris james weir  talia shadwell  june  kirkcaldie  stains department store to become david jones stuff   jones david  biographical entry australian dictionary of biography retrieved  february    a b c david jones limited   guide to australian business records retrieved  may    httpwwwnewcastlenswgovaudataassetspdffileheritagewalkfurtherinfopdf  encyclopedia of australian art alan mcculloch hutchinson of london    jan   music and drama the american scene—widespread u nlagovau   annual report to shareholders  the adelaide steamship company  mcmahon stephen  march  david jones profit dazzles retrieved  march    asx release  march  pdf wwwdavidjonescomau  march  retrieved  march    durie john  june  david jones ceo mark mcinnes resigns aft