has  stores located in most australian states and territories david jones main competitor is the larger midtoup market department store chain myer on  july  david jones will open their first new zealand store in wellington after buying kirkcaldie  stains in august  woolworths holdings announced that the david jones headquarters will be moved from sydney to richmond victoria owing to a combination of factors including rental lease fees and the market position for retailfashion as well as a lure from the victorian government contents  history  s  s  regional nsw  interstate entry  united states  david jones art gallery  dajonians repertory society  s  s  s  present  proposed myer merger  takeover by woolworths south africa  entry into new zealand  management  executive chairmen  nonexecutive chairmen  chief executive officers  branding  stores  credit and store cards  gallery  arms  see also  references  further reading  external links historyedit david jones and coy store corner of george street and barrack lane circa  david jones a welsh merchant met a hobart businessman charles appleton in london appleton had established a store in sydney in  and jones subsequently established a partnership with appleton moved to australia in  and the sydney store became known as appleton  jones when the partnership was dissolved in  jones moved his business to premises on the corner of george street and barrack lane jones survived the depression of the s and by  had retired from active management of the business a few years later when the firm failed he returned to manage its affairs and in a few years had fully discharged all obligations to his creditors by  the george street store had been rebuilt and a mail order facility introduced a factory was opened in marlborough street sydney to reduce reliance on imported goods on the death of the founder his son edward lloyd jones – led the company at eighteen years of age edward lloyd jones jnr – journeyed to england and entered the london office of david jones on his return to australia he gained pastoral and cattle experience in the burnett district of queensland he reentered the family business upon the death of his father in the train disaster at redfern in  david jones was then a private company but in  it became a public company edward lloyd jones jnr became chairman of directors and held that position until he resigned in  the elizabeth street store was opened in  under the guidance of chairman charles lloyd jones a further store was opened in market street sydney in  there was a small branch located in the australia hotel on martin place in  a state banquet was held for visiting queen elizabeth ii in the restaurant of the elizabeth street store s  sedit david jones flagship building on the corner of elizabeth street  market street sydney regional nsw  interstate entryedit within new south wales david jones established its first store in newcastle by acquiring scotts on hunter street in  closed  and  in wollongong the retailer walter lance  co in  david jones acquired and then converted the big w department stores at kotara fair and the two storey big w at warrawong in  the warrawong store closed in february  there was a store in wagga wagga due to the purchase of david copland  co in  closed  david jones expanded into victoria in  by acquiring the three stores of buckley  nunn located in bourke street northland and chadstone closed the latter in  in  david jones purchased the former gj coles store and building at  bourke street melbourne converting it into a david jones store david jones also owned the former georges store in collins street melbourne between  and  in south australia there were the acquisitions of charles birks  co adelaide in  and john martins adelaide in  in western australia acquired bon marche perth in  closed  foy  gibson in  closed  and aherns perth in  in queensland david jones purchased finney isles brisbane in  mckimmons townsville in  relocated from flinders street and then closed in  tc beirne brisbane in  marsh  webster mackay in  closed  bolands cairns also in  relocated to earlsville in  since closed wyper bros bundaberg in  closed  and stuparts maryborough in  closed  united statesedit in  david jones acquired a group of  stores in the united states called buffums these were ultimately rolled into adelaide steamship company and closed by that company in may  david jones art galleryedit a significant feature of the elizabeth street shop contributing greatly to its aura of quality and exclusivity was the david jones art gallery founded in  directors included will ashton – marion hall best – john amory – m p ferrandiere – george duncan – robert haines – brian moore – and peta phillips  among the many drawcards was the dobell exhibition of  the duke of bedfords collection in  and the mendel collection of modern painting also in  many of the prominent arts societies which held annual exhibitions there included the australian art society the society of artists australian watercolour institute contemporary art society and society of sculptors and associates prize exhibitions held in the gallery included those sponsored by w d  h o wills and transfield dajonians repertory societyedit throughout the s and s the sydney store supported the dajonians repertory society a staff club amateur theatre group their plays were variously performed in the david jones theatrette and such theatres as st james hall and independent theatre they engaged the services of a permanent producer carl francis throughout the s and frederick hughes from  and produced six plays a year mostly light comedies by recognised playwrights such as j b priestley through this time the company was led by sir charles lloyd jones until his death in  by  the store network had expanded to eight stores with expansion focused upon the burgeoning new suburbs of sydney s  sedit in  the adelaide steamship company headed by john spalvins acquired a substantial interest in dav