ia developers cookie statement mobile view how to sell your products to retail outlets such as david jones  quorathis page may be out of date save your draft before refreshing this pagesubmit any pending changes before refreshing this page hide this messagequorasign in david jones company ecommerce marketing retail marketing ecommerce businesshow do you sell your products to retail outlets such as david jonesupdatecancelpromoted by heapheap is like google analytics but its made for saas appsheap automatically tracks every action eg click swipe pageview users take in your web applearn more at heapanalyticscomanswer wiki answers simon huggins former product manager for sap hybris ecommerce suiteanswered w agoyou need to get your product known in smaller outlets first prove you have something that is growing in popularity yearonyear and try to get market data on the demographics  geography of people who are buying the product so that the retailer can understand that they are not taking on risk by introducing the product and are likely to be making money from their very valuable use of shelf space bear in mind that if they adopt your product then they are having to deny someone else that space so you need to know your competition to ensure you offer something that incumbents in the market are not or that you are introducing something that is genuinely new and there is a proven trend of adoption in the broader marketalternatively get backing from an existing company or financial backer that has presence in that market already  either financial investment or see if you can get them to adopt your product but youll have to go through the same kind of exercise with them more than likelybe careful though  you will need to also prove that you can upscale your operation to provide a larger quantity on demand which may require substantial financial outlay and if your product is summarily dumped then you may have a lot of overheads loans etc but no market to shift your products to  once you get engaged in this scale of market you are at the mercy of the retailers and they will do what they can to reduce your profit margin in favor of making money themselves leaving you with potentially reduced opportunity to further upscaleyou are much better to gradually upscale through smaller retailers  you expose yourself to less risk from large retail outlets get a grass roots following and get to plan your upscaling in a more measured wayalso why the internet is your friend  why not concentrate on this market  its much less risky and again easier to upscale according to demand  reach into new marketsbe very very careful retail is not a market for the fainthearted views · answer requested by  personpromoted by chartiohow is your startup doing get started with data analytics nowconnect all your business data in one place try chartio for free and get to new insights in minutesstart now at chartiocomsignuprelated questionsmore answers belowhow do brands make deals with retail outlets to have the stores carry their productswhat advantages and disadvantages are there for retail outlets selling similar products to be located close togetherwhat is used bi companies to sell a particular product at a retail outleti buy my product from a factory at £ sell online for £ at what wholesale price should i sell to retail storeshow do you convince a large retail outlet to stock a product you want to sell to them that you get from overseas dan saad  years of ecommerce merchandising marketing and startups  drop shippinganswered w agoas others have commented  you can get in direct contact with the buying department and send them information however sometimes the larger the retailer the harder it is to even get an opportunity to even have your product reviewedone of the best ways to get your product reviewed is to hire a sales company that already has good contacts and track record and knows the correct people to get your product reviewed by depending on the industry theses outside salesmen may be called manufacturers representatives or brokers they are usually  paid on a commission basis only views ·  upvote · answer requested by  person steve waddington ceo director cio engineering manageranswered w agomany years go i used to sell retail systems to large department store chains colesmyer being one  you just need to get in touch with their purchasing department  large chains like that have a whole department with specialist purchasing officers and managers for their various product lines   just ring up their head office and ask to be put through to the purchasing department then explain what your product is and they will either connect you or give you the contact details of the person you need to talk to viewsview more answersrelated questionswhat is the relationship between flipkart and ws retailwhat are the online and offline retail outlets to sell my innovative product in indiahow do counter sales retail outlets calculate there profit as the number of different products they have  each product have different profit do you work in retail whats a product that sells like crazy in your storehow can i track the selling in my outlet where one of my worker sits and sell my product and collect the payment in cash food productwhich department do you have to talk too to sell a retail productis the best price by walmart does not violate the rules by selling their products to retail customers in indiawhat are the types of retails outletshow do i sell software products for indian retailerswhich retail outlets in india sell kindlerelated questionshow do brands make deals with retail outlets to have the stores carry their productswhat advantages and disadvantages are there for retail outlets selling similar products to be located close togetherwhat is used bi companies to sell a particular product at a retail outleti buy my product from a factory at £ sell online for £ at what wholesale price should i sell to retail storeshow do you convince a 